Assignments

1. (hint:if-else): 
Write a java program called EvalutionService which provides a method callled 'evaluateSubjectMarks(int subjectMarks)', that will print "PASS" if the int variable "subjectMarks" is more than or equal to 50; or prints "FAIL" otherwise.

Write a test java program (EvalutionServiceTest.java etc)which includes main method to test above class & method.


2. (hint: if-else): 
Write a java program called NumberService which provides a method callled 'evaluateNumber(int number)', that will  print "Odd Number" if the int variable “number” is odd, or “Even Number” otherwise.

Write a test java program which includes main method to test above class & method.


3). (hint : Switch stament): Enhance the above class to include 'printNumberInWord(int number)' which prints "ONE", "TWO",... , "NINE", "OTHER" if the int variable "number" is 1, 2,... , 9, or other, respectively. Use  "switch-case" statement.

Create a test class to test the above









